TI - Enhanced degradation of <prot>  EGF </prot>  receptors by a sorting <prot>  nexin </prot>  , <prot>  SNX1 </prot>  .
PG - 1008 - 10 AB - The vectorial movement of proteins requires specific recognition by components of the vesicular trafficking machinery .
A protein , <p1  pair=1 >  <p1  pair=3 >  <prot>  sorting nexin - 1 </prot>  </p1>  </p1>  ( <p1  pair=2 >  <p1  pair=4 >  <prot>  SNX1 </prot>  </p1>  </p1>  ) , was identified in a human cell line that bound to a region of the <p2  pair=1 >  <p2  pair=2 >  <prot>  epidermal growth factor receptor </prot>  </p2>  </p2>  ( <p2  pair=3 >  <p2  pair=4 >  <prot>  EGFR </prot>  </p2>  </p2>  ) containing the lysosomal targeting code .
 <prot> SNX1 </prot>  contains a region of homology to a yeast vacuolar sorting protein , and overexpression of <prot>  SNX1 </prot>  decreased the amount of <prot>  EGFR </prot>  on the cell surface as a result of enhanced rates of constitutive and ligand - induced degradation .
Thus , <prot>  SNX1 </prot>  is likely to play a role in sorting <prot>  EGFR </prot>  to lysosomes .
